table: Philippines, Davao, 7 km (4.3 mi) SW of Magsaysay
Ten students hospitalized and power outages in various areas of Davao del Sur.
Myanmar, Ayeyarwady, 15 km (9.3 mi) S of Nyaungdon
Several houses, a monastery and a pagoda collapsed and several religious buildings damaged in the epicentral area.
Chile, Antofagasta, 98 km (61 mi) S of Calama, Chile
Rockfalls occurred and power cables damaged at a mine in the epicentral area.
Indonesia, South Sulawesi, 78 km (48 mi) E of Masamba
One mosque collapsed, two schools and one home damaged in East Luwu Regency.
Philippines, Soccsksargen, 0 km (0 mi) ENE of Banisilan
Two people injured, more than 564 houses destroyed and 69 structures damaged in the Wao area.
Armenia, Lori, 3 km (1.9 mi) ENE of Sarahart
One house collapsed and one building damaged in the Artik-Spitak area.
Norway, Svalbard and Jan Mayen offshore, 34 km (21 mi) NE of Olonkinbyen
Iraq, Dohuk, 37 km (23 mi) E of Çukurca, Turkey
At least 20 homes destroyed and many others damaged in Yüksekova District, Turkey.
Kyrgyzstan, Osh, 4 km (2.5 mi) WNW of Osh
One structure collapsed and 39 others damaged in Kara-Suu-Alay area.
Italy, Campania offshore, 1 km (0.62 mi) S of Monte di Procida
Eleven people injured and many buildings including a church damaged in the Naples area.
Indonesia, West Java offshore, 64 km (40 mi) SW of Palabuhanratu
One home destroyed in Lebak Regency.
Mexico, Oaxaca, 5 km (3.1 mi) W of San Pedro Tidaá
Four people injured and a gas leak occurred in Mexico City.
Indonesia, North Sumatra, 41 km (25 mi) ENE of Sibolga
Chile, Coquimbo, 13 km (8.1 mi) SSE of Coquimbo
One building collapsed in La Serena and a sinkhole appeared in the Coquimbo area.
Peru, Arequipa, 2 km (1.2 mi) SE of Maca
At least 20 homes destroyed, 47 others and a church damaged and roads affected in the Achoma-Lari-Maca area.
Iran, Isfahan, 43 km (27 mi) W of Ardestān
Several homes and a caravanserai collapsed and many buildings damaged in the Natanz area.
Panama, Chiriquí, 123 km (76 mi) SSE of Burica
At least 13 structures damaged in Chiriquí, Herrera, and Veraguas provinces.
United States, Alaska, 88 km (55 mi) SSE of Adak
New Zealand, Southland offshore, 170 km (110 mi) WSW of Riverton
Minor damage to the Dunedin Gasworks Museum.[143] A tsunami with a height of 10 cm (3.9 in) was observed in southwest Fiordland.
